      "content": "Tariffs are a highly debated topic, and the reality is they can be a double-edged sword. Proponents argue they protect domestic jobs from unfair foreign competition, which is a valid goal for national industry. However, critics point out that tariffs often lead to higher prices for consumers because businesses pass those added costs along, ultimately hurting regular people. The net effect depends heavily on how the tariffs are structured and who is ultimately bearing the cost.",
