      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The long-term health of a nation is best served by a strategic blend of both, leaning heavily toward robust, managed trade. A pure free-trade model leaves domestic industries vulnerable to exploitation and offshoring, which erodes the economic base of the country. Therefore, a smart, protectionist approach—using targeted tariffs and subsidies to build up strategic domestic capabilities—is essential for ensuring national resilience against global economic shocks.",
      "source": "target",
